    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large wide-based <strong>oven-proof pan</strong> (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and <strong>pepper strips</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 7-8 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Crack your <strong>eggs </strong>into a large bowl with your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>chopped parsley</strong>, 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Whisk it all together – this is your <strong>egg mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
